main event: On 21 November 1963, three solid objects were observed in the sky over West Nyack, New York, showing signs of high-speed maneuvering.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be solid bodies and were sharply outlined in the sky,They maneuvered at an estimated speed of 500 mph,The objects traced a 45-degree arc within about 5 seconds,The objects ultimately disappeared from the radar scope,This incident is documented in Project Blue Book.
sighted object: three solid objects in the sky
